# VSAccountManagerResult

**Class**

An object that represents a request made for subscriber account information.

## Declaration

```swift
class VSAccountManagerResult
```

## Overview

The system returns this object to your app when you app calls [doc://com.apple.videosubscriberaccount/documentation/VideoSubscriberAccount/VSAccountManager/enqueue(_:completionHandler:)]. Use this object to cancel the request with [doc://com.apple.videosubscriberaccount/documentation/VideoSubscriberAccount/VSAccountManagerResult/cancel()] while the request is in progress.

## Cancelling a Request

- **cancel()**: Cancels an in-progress request for subscriber account information.

## Enqueuing requests

- **enqueue(_:completionHandler:)**: Submits a request for subscriber account information.
- **VSAccountMetadataRequest**: An object that specifies what subscriber account information your app retrieves.
- **VSAccountMetadata**: A collection of information for a subscriber’s account.
- **VSAccountProviderResponse**: An object that contains the response from the account provider.
- **VSAccountProviderAuthenticationScheme**: Authentication schemes for account provider requests and responses.

## Inherits From

- NSObject

## Conforms To

- CVarArg
- CustomDebugStringConvertible
- CustomStringConvertible
- Equatable
- Hashable
- NSObjectProtocol
